result.execSummary:
The defendant Moira L.K. Poupart was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 2:39 PM Defendant Moira L.K. Poupart appeared by video, in custody in the Oneida County Jail.  Attorney Courtney Christine Jolin in court for Moira L.K. Poupart.  Attorney Karl Peter Hayes in court for State of Wisconsin. Right to be personally present at today's hearing explained to defendant.  Defendant confirms that she would like to proceed without being personally present in court.  Court finds that defendant agreeing to proceed by phone/video means, and waiving right to be personally present in court for today's proceedings.  State motions to amend count 1 to remove repeater enhancer.  Court grants motion.  Plea of Guilty to amended Count 1.  Plea questionnaire filed.  Rights given.  Court finds that defendant is knowingly and voluntarily waiving right to jury trial and plea is found to be entered knowingly and voluntarily.  Found guilty. Court imposes 20 days in county jail, 4 days credit.  May be served with Huber privileges.  May be served in Oneida County.  Costs imposed of $443.  Due to the Clerk of Courts within 60 days.
